- Creating a New Project:

	\ npx react-native init MyProjectName (before starting Android Emulator on Genymotion)

	\ react-native run-android (after starting Android Emulator)

	\ react-native start (starts application and bundle)

	\ react-native start --reset-cache (when you need to start application and bundle with a new cache)

-*-*-*-*-

- ESLint, Prettier and EditorConfig: code patterns

	\ yarn add eslint -D

	\ yarn eslint --init

	\ yarn add prettier eslint-config-prettier eslint-plugin-prettier babel-eslint -D

- React Navigation: manages routes (https://reactnavigation.org/docs/getting-started/)

	\ yarn add react-navigation

	\ yarn add react-native-screens react-native-safe-area-context

	\ yarn add react-navigation-stack

- Styled Components: appliees css styles on Components

	\ yarn add styled-components

- React-Native Vector Icons: svg icons!

	\ yarn add react-native-vector-icons

- React-Native Gesture Handler: provides some build Components, like buttons, regardless whether the device is Android, iOS...

	\ yarn add react-native-gesture-handler

- Axios: calls apis

	\ yarn add axios

- Async Storage: it's like localStorage, but for mobile

	\ yarn add @react-native-community/async-storage

- Prop Types: Types and Validations for Properties

	\ yarn add prop-types

-*-*-*-*-

- Genymotion: Android Emulator. There are some issues using Genymotion and Docker together on Windows, so take care!!

- Reactotron: debugger for React-Native Mobile Projects. It's a software that you download and a package that you add with yarn.

	\ yarn add reactotron-react-native -D